WEBVTT

00:00:00.300 --> 00:00:02.836
Oral counseling is a type of meeting that occurs between a

00:00:02.902 --> 00:00:05.338
Supervisor and a Bargaining Unit Employee.

00:00:05.405 --> 00:00:08.942
It is to be used constructively to warn a Bargaining Unit

00:00:09.008 --> 00:00:12.412
Employee about conduct or performance.

00:00:12.479 --> 00:00:15.648
It can prevent the need for disciplinary action.

00:00:15.715 --> 00:00:18.284
Article 8 explains the difference between a routine

00:00:18.351 --> 00:00:21.855
counseling session and meetings that an Employee is entitled to

00:00:21.921 --> 00:00:24.791
have a Union Representative attend.

00:00:24.858 --> 00:00:28.795
This article also covers rules for retaining written counseling records.


